<HEADLINE> Experts Warn of Computer Virus Dubbed "THUS" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 7 (Xinhua) -- China's leading anti-virus
company, the Rising Computer Technology, warned computer users
that a killer virus dubbed "THUS" may attack computer hard drives
on December 13.
</P>
<P>
Liu Xu, an anti-virus expert, suggested computer users delete
the virus with anti-virus software before December 13 or change
the date.  
</P>
